Decisions Made
- Hardened the shell-based skill orchestration harness by validating that each check object defines exactly one supported matcher key.
- Made ordered snippet matching resilient under `set -euo pipefail` by preventing a missing `grep` match from aborting before the explicit failure path.

Problems Encountered
- The previous regression-harness PR was already merged, so the follow-up had to be cut as a new branch and PR from the updated main branch.
- A parallel HEAD lookup raced with the commit and returned the pre-commit SHA, so the note/push flow had to re-read the current commit.

Constraints Identified
- The fix should remain limited to the merged harness file so the follow-up PR stays narrowly scoped.
- The shell harness must keep using the existing variables and failure path semantics while avoiding premature exits under strict shell options.

Open Questions
- Whether to add a tiny negative fixture that intentionally violates the single-key rule so this validation itself is covered by automation.
- Whether the harness should eventually support richer matcher types beyond contains/absent/ordered_contains.

Context
- Follow-up to merged PR #24. Updated tests/skill-orchestration-harness.sh, reran bash tests/skill-orchestration.sh and bash tests/all.sh, and prepared this patch as a new PR because the original branch had already merged.
